cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ST, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper discusses the use of Gaussian Processes for modeling time-series data and proposes two relational kernel learning methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also deals with real-world data sets, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
